						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup in the field known as <hi rend="italic">suḍugāḍagaddi.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that when Mallidēva was ruling granted two <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of wet land to a person named Bommaya.</p>						

						<p>The record, in characters of about the 13th century A.D., is dated in the cyclic year Khara, Chaitra, śu. 15 Thursday. The cyclic year Khara occurred twice-(1) Śaka 1153 (1231 A.D.) and (2) Śaka 1213 (1291 A.D.) in that century.</p>						

						</summary>
